parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Welding Failure in Fifth Wheel Area
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the welding in the fifth wheel area can cause the fifth wheel pin to fracture, leading to the separation of the fifth wheel from the frame, which can result in loss of control, accidents, or damage to the trailer and surrounding property.
symptoms: the fifth wheel separates from the frame
the bolts in the bed and kitchen area fail
the rear bumper cracks at the welds
the rear bumper with the spare tire mount folds down and drags on the highway.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The separation of the rear bumper from the frame can cause damage to the trailer and surrounding property, and potentially lead to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The rear bumper separates from the frame
the rear bumper cracks at the welds
the rear bumper with the spare tire mount folds down and drags on the highway.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The fracture of the frame can cause loss of control, accidents, or damage to the trailer and surrounding property.
symptoms: The front end of the frame fractures in two places near the main hitch area.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden failure of trailer tires can cause loss of control, accidents, and potentially lead to injuries or fatalities. The failure can also result in damage to the trailer and surrounding property.
symptoms: while driving at moderate to high speeds. The failure can occur on multiple tires within a short period

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the weld between the interior and exterior parts of the wheel rim can cause the wheel to separate, leading to loss of control, accidents, and potential injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The wheel rim breaks or separates
or difficulty steering; the wheel may come loose or fall off while driving.
